  "prompt": "Will I pass a drug test in 2 weeks as a non regular smoker?",
  "response": "The likelihood of passing a drug test in two weeks as a non-regular smoker can depend on several factors, including the type of drug, your metabolism, body fat, hydration level, and the sensitivity of the test. For example:\n\n- **THC (from marijuana)**: As a non-regular (infrequent) smoker, THC may be detectable in your urine for up to a week or two after use. However, individual circumstances can vary, so it might be possible to clear your system within two weeks.\n- **Other drugs**: The detection window for other substances varies considerably. For example, cocaine might be detectable for up to 3 days, while amphetamines can be found for about 2-5 days.\n\nIf you have only smoked occasionally and it has been a while since your last use, you might have a better chance of passing the test. Staying hydrated, engaging in regular exercise, and maintaining a healthy diet can potentially help expedite the detox process. However, the most reliable way to ensure passing a drug test is to refrain from drug use entirely.\n\nIt's important to consult medical professionals or substance abuse experts for personalized advice and support.",
